entries.meaning: Of, pertaining to, or undergoing transmigration, as a soul from one body to another.
examples: I think of him as of some transmigratory votary of Indian legend, who says, "Though I be dog, or jackal, or pismire, in the last rudiments of nature, under what integument or ferocity, I cleave to right, as the sure ladder that leads up to man and to God."

entries.meaning: Of, pertaining to, or undergoing transmigration, as between places.
examples: [T]he Kuala Gula Bird Sanctuary offers a hideaway to see some of the transmigratory birds that regular flock to the area.
